### Multi Map — Feature TODO

### Consult the how-todo skill for instructions for reading this file. 

- A living document for proposed features, improvements, and design intentions.
- Add items freely. Expand into detail before implementation.
- Items are ordered by dependency and recommended execution sequence.

---

### [ ] Phase 1: The Data & Identity Layer
- Agent Context: firestore.rules, multi-map-core.js (data manager), multi-map-library.js, auth.js, Firebase Admin functions.

### [ ] 1. Project Directory Cleanup & Data Integrity
- Intent: Enforce a strict single-directory rule per project to ensure database cleanliness and prevent recursive navigation issues.
- Details:
  - Run a migration/cleanup script to identify and repair legacy projects with multiple directories or directories pointing to other projects.
  - Selecting a project in the data-manager should make its unique directory the active map.
  - Enforce logic ensuring the project directory only has one pointer to each unique page in the project.

### [ ] 2. Refine Map Sharing & Read-Only Views
- Intent: Refine the existing map-sharing system and polish the read-only `view.html` experience.
- Details:
  - Improve the `view.html` page to provide a seamless read-only map mode (stripping out inspector panels and editing event listeners, but keeping limitted smart button and navigation features from multi-map-core.js).
  - Ensure shared maps show a robust "Fork to my workspace" button for authenticated visitors. When forked, full content of original map/project will need to be imported as a fresh project for a fully functional workspace.
  - Add expiry options for shared links (7 / 30 / 90 days).
  - *Cross-Reference:* This system will be heavily revisited and integrated with Cloud Storage Vaults (Task 4), P2P Federation pointers (Task 7), and Colab-Root Shared Spaces (Task 12).

---

### [ ] Phase 2: The Portal & Agent Paradigm Shift
- Agent Context: phase-engines.js, engines/*, mapstate-schema.json, Portal logic (multi-map-core.js), AI Agent prompt definitions.

### [ ] 3. File-Root Maptype & Local File System Explorer
- Intent: Create a map-native local file-system explorer for seamless local file management within Multi-Map.
- Specification: feature-specs/file-root-spec.md
- Details:
  - Integrate file-root maptypes into mapstate-schema.json.
  - Utilize the browser's HTML5 File System Access API (where supported) to read local directory structures and represent them as dynamic child nodes.
  - Build a corresponding phase engine (engines/file-explorer.html) and register it in phase-engines.js. It should provide a specialized viewport for viewing, organizing, and executing basic file operations.
  - *Cross-Reference:* Establishes the baseline for external file mapping to be expanded in Task 4.

### [ ] 4. Third-Party Cloud Storage Integrations & Cloud Sync
- Intent: Extend the file system mapping capabilities to interact with external cloud drives and enable per-page/per-project cloud syncing.
- Specification: feature-specs/third-party-cloud-spec.md
- Details:
  - Add "Cloud Sync" button to projects and pages (project syncing applies to all pages). Marking for cloud sync adds it to the cloud vault (Firestore/BYO-storage) respecting quotas.
  - Add an "All Vaults" option to Data Vault dropdown showing all available projects sorted by category (local only, local cloud synced, cloud only).
  - Implement authentication and API bridging for services like Google Drive and Google Docs. Expand Firebase Auth providers in auth.js to request Drive OAuth scopes.
  - Enable syncing, fetching, and map-native representation of external cloud files. Ensure OAuth tokens and API limits are handled safely (utilizing functions/middleware/rateLimit.js).
  - *Cross-Reference:* Integrates with Map Sharing (Task 2) to allow permissions mapping for cloud-vault maps.

### [ ] 5. Flowchart Upgrades & Flow-Phase-Engine
- Intent: Expand the flowchart maptype to natively support dynamic portal passing and phase engine visualization for complex decision logic.
- Details:
  - Upgrade all flow-type nodes to act as portals. 
  - `Process` = generic payload link.
  - `Decision` = flow-logic-root map with metadata that returns T/F or values based on internal logic.
  - `Terminal` = flow-io-root map with sub-types for building UI in/out or data/metadata pass (e.g., text entry, file download, yes/no). Calls a modal for user interaction and returns to the flow.
  - Generate a new `Flow-Phase-Engine` with play/pause/stop/skip controls to visually walk through the flowchart, auto-expanding connections and calling map logic/payloads as it traverses.

### [ ] 6. Sectional Text Editing in Prompt/Agent Engines
- Intent: Improve the text-editing experience for prompt and agent maptypes directly inside their phase engine views.
- Details:
  - Allow sectional text editing with dynamic updating directly in the prompt and agent phase engine views.
  - This bridges the gap between spatial map building and raw text document editing.

### [ ] 7. Launch True Federation (WebRTC + CRDTs)
- Intent: Transition Multi-Map from a centralized Firebase payload host to a true peer-to-peer (P2P) federated network, relegating Firebase strictly to an identity and WebRTC signaling switchboard.
- Specification: feature-specs/launch-federation-spec.md
- Details:
  - Transition the local memory map states (state.nodes) to a CRDT framework (like Yjs or Automerge).
  - Implement WebRTC signaling using Firebase Firestore to exchange connection offers and ICE candidates between peers.
  - Shift the primary network transport for live collaborative map edits from Firestore onSnapshot to direct P2P WebRTC data channels.
  - Ensure data persistence fallbacks utilize the user's primary "Vault" (Drive/Local OS).
  - *Cross-Reference:* Replaces the central payload storage in Task 2 (Map Sharing) with lightweight pointers (owner_uid + map_id), serving shared maps directly from the peer network. Serves as the networking foundation for Colab-Roots (Task 12).

---

### [ ] Phase 3: Core Mechanics & Interaction Stability
- Agent Context: multi-map-core.js, multi-map-rules.js, Keyboard event listeners, functions/index.js.

### [ ] 8. Multi-Level Undo / Redo Polish
- Intent: Implement a multi-level undo/redo system that persists across the new dynamic portal navigations.
- Details:
  - Isolate undo/redo state arrays inside the kernel map object (e.g., window.kernel.maps[map_id].history) instead of a global array.
  - On enterPortal, push the current state onto the child map's history; the parent map's history is frozen but preserved. On exitPortal, restore the parent map's history stack.
  - Redo stack: clear the redo stack for a specific map when a new action is taken (e.g., inside saveHistory()).
  - Cap history depth at 50 entries per map to limit memory.
  - Keyboard: Bind Ctrl/Cmd+Z = undo, Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+Z = redo to the global key listener.
  - Show current undo depth as a subtle counter on the undo button (↩️ 3).

### [ ] 9. Keyboard & Clipboard Polish
- Intent: Refine keyboard editing interactions and implement robust cross-platform copy/cut/paste logic.
- Details:
  - Update text-box interaction: Only "enter" should commit a title box when selected after new-node generation. Wait for user to finish typing or press enter again to skip.
  - Implement `Ctrl+X` to clip/cut nodes (using existing clip logic). Fix current clipping bug where modal launches but returns "Clip failed. The node may not be clippable."
  - Native paste logic: paste as a targeted portal.
  - Off-platform paste logic: paste full text of the clipped branch.
  - Internal paste logic: insert children in layers naturally, respecting auto-arrange geometry (unless tagged for specific meaning) as if created by the user.

### [ ] 10. Phase Engine Interaction & UI Sync
- Intent: Ensure dynamic portals and radial menus render seamlessly across different phase engine views.
- Details:
  - Update Sidebar Phase Engine rendering: If a portal's payload triggers a phase engine render, and that portal is selected, selecting the phase engine from the sidebar should show the payload's phase-specific rendering (as if that page's root were selected).
  - Only show that phase engine as accessible if that portal is selected, unless the hosting page map can also be rendered in that phase.
  - Bring Radial Menu editing and smart button navigation natively into the Orbital Focus engine.
  - *Cross-Reference:* Ensures UI syncing for the new Flow-Phase-Engine introduced in Task 5.

### [ ] 11. Unified Search & AI UX Polish
- Intent: Unify global node search with the AI widget, creating a single intelligent interface for navigation and generation, while refining AI intent parsing.
- Details:
  - Integrate cross-map semantic search directly into the AI interface. Selecting a cross-map result opens/creates a portal to that page and fires selectNode().
  - Implement Tier 1 local fuzzy search (Fuse.js in multi-map-library.js) and Tier 2 AI Semantic Search (/api/search endpoint in functions/index.js for vector-searching log-stored maps).
  - Make text selectable/copyable in the chat interface. Users should be able to select and copy individual words/segments of old prompts, responses, error messages, etc.
  - Teach intent parser to intelligently choose between search, edit, generation, and, for generation tasks, the best map-type if none is explicitly provided. Allow the AI to identify desired actions (insertion via portal, new page, expand current node, etc.) directly from the prompt without explicit clarification unless strictly necessary.
  - *Cross-Reference:* Default out-of-scope AI intents to the Wiki/Links system being expanded in Task 13.

---

### [ ] Phase 4: Social & Collaborative Expansion
- Agent Context: engines/colab-engine.html, engines/person.html, multi-map-library.js, Realtime Database/Firestore Listeners, firestore.rules.

### [ ] 12. Colab-Root, Communities, & Shared Spaces
- Intent: Introduce an entirely new colab-root system that acts as a dedicated container for social networks, communities, and collaborative spaces.
- Specification: feature-specs/contacts-communities-spec.md
- Details:
  - Introduce a new colab-root maptype and a dedicated phase engine (engines/colab-engine.html) to manage organizational structures, shared maps, and user roles.
  - Introduce organizational sub-types: colab-organization, colab-community, and colab-group. Update mapstate-schema.json.
  - Incorporate existing person objects (contacts, user profiles) as sub-types or dynamically reference them via portals inside the colab-root.
  - Update firestore.rules heavily to enforce Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) based on the acl metadata for colab-root nodes.
  - *Cross-Reference:* Connects multiplayer instances securely utilizing the WebRTC P2P mesh established in Task 7. Greatly expands upon the basic read-only sharing established in Task 2.

---

### [ ] Phase 5: Platform Delivery & Documentation
- Agent Context: service-worker.js, manifest.json, multi-map-tutorials.js, wiki.html.

### [ ] 13. Robust Wiki & Auto-Driven Tutorial System
- Intent: Build a robust, map-native Wiki alongside an automated tutorial system to document the finished architecture.
- Details:
  - Substantially expand wiki.html to act as the central documentation hub, linking directly to map states and tutorials in tutorials/*.json.
  - Refine multi-map-tutorials.js to parse new autoNav and autoSelect fields.
  - Connect autoNav to PhaseEngine.switchView() (from phase-engines.js) and autoSelect to the node selection logic in multi-map-core.js.
  - Implement CSS spotlight overlays (in multi-map-ui.css) to highlight specific DOM elements during tutorial steps.
  - Add step validators in multi-map-tutorials.js: the "Next" button only activates once the user successfully completes the requested UI interaction.
  - Persist tutorial progress to localStorage to survive page refreshes.

### [ ] 14. PWA / Offline Mode
- Intent: Package the app as a Progressive Web App so it can be installed natively and continue working on flaky connections.
- Details:
  - Add a Web App Manifest (manifest.json): app name, icons, theme color, display: standalone.
  - Implement a service-worker.js with a cache-first strategy for all static assets (HTML, JS, CSS, phase engines, tutorial/wiki JSON).
  - Tie IndexedDB caching into multi-map-library.js fetch routines so active project maps are readable/editable offline.
  - Sync queue: changes made offline are written to a local queue and flushed to Firestore when connectivity returns (using the Background Sync API).
  - Add an offline indicator in the nav bar and an "Install Multi-Map" prompt after 3 sessions.